                                        "},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In a list of n contradictory statements, there's at most 1 truth among them. So the possibilities are 0 or 1 truth, equivalent to 0 or 1 Knight speaking it. If there's no Knights among the three, then the unspoken truth should be "Exactly 0 of us is a knave", with both suppositions contradicting each other (all 3 are either a Knight or a knave). Therefore, it should be the case where one of them is telling the truth as a Knight, and that would be Bernard who claims the existence of 2 knaves among them, talking about knave Andrew and knave Charlie."}]},{"type":"text","text":"



